      <h1 class="celtic celtic-h1 celtic-color text-center">About</h1>
      <p>The Virtual Gaeltacht is a free online platform for learners of Irish to meet and chat with others.</p>
      <p>The conversations place focus on three overlooked aspects of language acquisition: The Three Es</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Emotion</li>
        <li>Empathy</li>
        <li>Engagement</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Emotion is at the core of every story we tell, even the simplest, beginner-level ones about waking up and leaving the house. We express these stories, and empathise with others, through both verbal and non-verbal gestures. With our eyes, we engage and demonstrate the focus of our attention.</p>
      <p>
      <p>The Virtual Gaeltacht combines The Three Es with the latest web application technologies to create an environment where Irish conversations thrive.</p>
      <p>Learners control their own avatar in a group chat where they have full control over gaze, facial expressions and gestures.</p>
      <p>Feel free to give it a try.</p>
